Spring core: 
============
=> It is base module in spring framework.
 -> It provides fundamental concept of spring framework.
    1. IoC container(Inversion of Control)
    2. Dependency Injection
    3. Bean LifeCycle
    4. Bean Scopes
    5. Autowiring

Spring Context:
===============
=> It will deal wit configurations required for our Spring Application.

Spring AOP:   --> Aspect Oriented Programming
===========

=> AOP is used to separate bussiness logic and secondary logic .
  Ex: Security, Logging , auditing, Exception Handling etc...

Note: If we combine bussiness logic & secondary logic then we will face maintence issues of our project.

Spring JDBC:
============
=> Spring JDBC is used to simplify Database communication logic.
=> in java jdbc, we need to write boiler plate code
    
    > Load Driver
    > Get Connection
    > Create Statement
    > Execute Query
    >Close Connection
==> Using Spring JDBC we can directly execute query the remaining part Spring JDBC will take care.

Spring MVC:
===========
=> It is used to develop both Web application and Distributed application
=> Web Application(C to B)
 Ex: gmail, Facebook etc....

=> Distributed Application (B to C) / Web services or Restful Services

  Ex: IRCTC --- MAKEMYTRIP
      Passport -- Aadhar Card

Spring ORM
==========
=> ORM-> Object Relational Mapping
=> Spring Framework having integration with ORM frameworks.
     Ex. Spring ORM, Spring Data JPA etc...
NOTE: JDBC will represent the data in text format where as Hibernate ORM will represent data in Object format.

Spring Security
===============
=> Security is very crusial for every application.
=> By using Spring Security, We can implement both authentication and authorization.
=> Spring Security with O.AUTH2.0
=> Spring Security with JWT.(JSON WEB TOKENS)

 Spring Batch
=============
=> Batch means bulk operations.
=>Sending monthly statement to customers in email
=> Sending reminders to customers Bulk msg

Spring Cloud : It provides some commom tools to quickly build distributed systems.
============
=> It provides service registry to register all our microservices at one place. 
=> It provides load balancer to balance load of our application.
=> It provides monitoring facilities.
=> It provides API gateway to have single entry point for all our apis.
=> Routing.
=> It provides Circuit breakers(Fault tolerance Systems/Resillence).
=> Distributed messaging .

Spring Test:
===========
=> It provides Unit Test Framework.





































































































